To print the string containing the escaped character represented by `\x9b`, which corresponds to the ASCII bell (BEL) character, you can use the following code snippet in Python:

```python
print("\\x9b")
```

When executed, this will display the ASCII bell character on the console. Remember that escaping backslashes themselves requires additional backslashes (`\\`) in strings within many programming languages like Python. ```python
# This line prints the ASCII bell character represented by '\x9b'
print("\\x9b")
```

By running this code, you should see a notification sound played once on most terminal emulators, as the output triggers the BEL character. Keep in mind that actual audible feedback might depend on your system settings and environment.
